{{Top|leg}}
The '''quetarra''' was a [[Zabrak/Legends|Zabrak]] [[Music/Legends|musical]] instrument that had eight strings and mutiple holes. The mad [[Geneticist/Legends|genetic]] [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorist]] [[Zeta Magnus]] received a double-necked quetarra as payment for assisting in the [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetic]] reconstruction of a [[Unidentified horned cyborg|corniculate half-bot]].<ref name="swcw">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]''</ref> [[Zan Yant]] played one in the [[Rimsoo Seven cantina|casino]] at [[Republic Mobile Surgical Unit 7]] on [[Drongar/Legends|Drongar]] in [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]].<ref name="MSI:BS">''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Quetarra.jpg|thumb|right|A double-necked quetarra.]]
In a forum post on the [[Jedi Council Forums]], [[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story|SkyeWalkers]] author [[Abel G. Peña]] revealed that the intended identity of the corniculate half-bot Zeta Magnus reconstructed and received a quetarra as payment from was [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]]. This double-necked quetarra he received is a reference to the double-necked electric guitar Darth Maul plays in [[Randy Martinez]]'s "[https://www.randymartinez.art/fullscreen-page/comp-jj1r9r4n/c6038817-ef41-4438-9367-ebbfd89a4215/0/%3Fi%3D0%26p%3Dtp1ia%26s%3Dstyle-jj1r9r5d1 Sith Rocks]" illustration created for [[Celebration IV|Star Wars Celebration IV]].<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/52381816|board=Literature|thread=Abel G. Peña's "Skyewalkers" and "Lone Wolf"|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|date=2015-05-11|time=8:59 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314000518/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/abel-g-pe%C3%B1as-skyewalkers-and-lone-wolf.50027998/page-6}}</ref>

